<HEADLINE> Jiang Zemin on Damming of Yangtze   (19) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SANDOUPING (Three Gorges), November 8 (Xinhua) -- China
successful dammed the main course of the Yangtze today for the
Three Gorges Project, declared President Jiang Zemin at the
project site.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at a ceremony after the blocking of the Yangtze, Jiang
Zemin, also general secretary of the CPC Central Committee,
extended warm congratulations and cordial greetings to all project
constructors and described it as a great deed in China's endeavor
to achieve modernization and also a remarkable feat in the history
of the mankind to transform the nature and exploit natural
resources.
</P>
<P>
The damming of the Yangtze mainstream today signaled an end to
the first-phase construction of the Three Gorges Project, and the
start of the second phase, which will usher in the construction of
a mammoth Three Gorges Dam and power plants in the lot formed by
cofferdams.
</P>
<P>
"The age-old dream of the Chinese people to develop and
utilize the resources of the Three Gorges section of the Yangtze
has come closer to becoming true," said Jiang Zemin.
</P>
<P>
Reviewing the history related with the Three Gorges Project,
Jiang said the rapid economic growth and markedly increased
overall national strength since China initiated reform and
opening-up have enabled the country to undertake this
unprecedented cross-century project.
</P>
<P>
"The Three Gorges Project, the biggest water control and power
generation scheme in scale and with the most comprehensive and
widespread economy benefits, will greatly promote the development
of the Chinese national economy, and proved to be a lasting
exploit in the service of the present and future generations,"
said Jiang Zemin.
</P>
<P>
Jiang also called on all the participating units involved in
the project to redouble their efforts so as to ensure the
operation of the first power generating units in 2003. 
</P>
